<xs:element name="GoodsShipment">
  <xs:annotation>
    <xs:documentation>
      <details>H7 declaration goods.</details>
    </xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>
  <xs:complexType>
    <xs:sequence>
      <xs:element name="Consignment" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">
        <xs:complexType>
          <xs:sequence>
            <xs:element name="GoodsLocation" minOccurs="1">
              <xs:annotation>
                <xs:documentation>
                  <type>EUCDM 5.2</type>
                  <code>5/23</code>
                  <details>The location of goods. Mandatory for an I2 if not specified on initial pre-lodged H7 declaration. Valid combinations of GoodsLocation/TypeCode and GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode: - GoodsLocation/TypeCode 'A' (Designated place): - GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode: 'U' (UN/LOCODE) - GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode: 'V' (Customs office identifier) - GoodsLocation/TypeCode 'B' (Authorised place): - GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode: 'Y' (Authorisation number) This case is used if the goods are cleared through customs from MIO (temporary storage). - GoodsLocation/TypeCode 'C' (Approved place): - GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode: 'Z' (Free text - address) - GoodsLocation/TypeCode 'D' (Other): - GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode: 'Z' (Free text - address)</details>
                </xs:documentation>
              </xs:annotation>
              <xs:complexType>
                <xs:sequence>
                  <xs:element name="Name" type="ds:GoodsLocationNameTextType" minOccurs="0">
                    <xs:annotation>
                      <xs:documentation xml:lang="EN">Identification of location. If - GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode = 'U' this field should be the UN/LOCODE - GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode = 'V' this field should not be filled - GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode = 'Y' this field should be filled with the name of the location - GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode = 'Z' this field should be filled with the name of the location</xs:documentation>
                    </xs:annotation>
                  </xs:element>
                  <xs:element name="ID" type="ds:GoodsLocationIdentificationIDType" minOccurs="0">
                    <xs:annotation>
                      <xs:documentation>ID qualifier code. If - GoodsLocation/TypeCode = 'A' and GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode = 'U': Additional identifier of the UN/LOCODE - GoodsLocation/TypeCode = 'A' and GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode = 'V': Customs office ID - GoodsLocation/TypeCode = 'B' and GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode = 'Y': Authorisation number - GoodsLocation/TypeCode = 'C' and GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode = 'Z': This field should not be filled - GoodsLocation/TypeCode = 'D' and GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode = 'Z': This field should not be filled</xs:documentation>
                    </xs:annotation>
                  </xs:element>
                  <xs:element name="TypeCode" type="ds:GoodsLocationTypeCodeType" minOccurs="1">
                    <xs:annotation>
                      <xs:documentation>Type of location. - 'A': Designated place (can be combined with GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode: 'U' and 'V') - 'B': Authorised place (can be combined with GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode: 'Y') - 'C': Approved place (can be combined with GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode: 'Z') - 'D': Other (can be combined with GoodsLocation/Address/TypeCode: 'Z')</xs:documentation>
                    </xs:annotation>
                  </xs:element>
                  <xs:element name="Address">
                    <xs:complexType>
                      <xs:sequence>

                        </xs:element>
